column4: 500g chicken breast, 1 cup yogurt, 2 tsp garam masala, 1 tbsp lemon juice, 2 tbsp vegetable oil, 1 large onion, 2 garlic cloves, 1 tbsp grated ginger, 1 can diced tomatoes, 1 cup cream, 1 tsp turmeric, 1 tsp cumin, 1 tsp paprika, Salt, Fresh cilantro
column5: Marinate the chicken in yogurt, lemon juice, and spices for at least 1 hour. Grill until cooked. Saut√© onions, garlic, and ginger, then add spices and tomatoes. Cook until thickened. Add grilled chicken and cream. Simmer for 10 minutes. Garnish with cilantro and serve with rice or naan.

column4: 400g spaghetti, 2 large eggs, 100g pancetta, 2 plump garlic cloves, 50g pecorino cheese, 50g parmesan, Black pepper
column5: Cook the spaghetti. Beat the eggs in a bowl and combine with the two cheeses. Fry the pancetta with garlic. Combine everything together, adding a bit of pasta water to create a creamy sauce. Season with pepper and serve.
